<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496675>
    dc:description "Fig. 14. Thesium quartzicolum: (A) habit and substrate of female plants, (B) habit and quartz-silcrete substrate of male plants, (C) an amplified view of female plants displaying fruiting jointed branchlets, (D) a shoot showing scale-like bracts and bracteoles subtending fruits, (E) a male shoot displaying 4-merous flower and stamen, (F) female flowering twig, (G) detailed floral parts in relation to scally leaf, cartilaginous bract and bracteole margins, (H) longitudinal section of floral parts.Photographs:Daniel Zhigila." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10496675/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

